The paper discusses the use of multiagent models and evolutionary algorithms for calibration, which are commonly used in the field of multiagent systems (cs.MA). The focus is on geographical models, which falls under the category of computational engineering (cs.CE) and spatial informatics (cs.SI). The use of distributed computing is also mentioned, which is relevant to the field of distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the model to historical situations, which could fall under the category of graphics (cs.GR) if visualization techniques are used.
